岗位职责:
1、负责建立和完善公司人力资源管理制度体系;
2、根据公司发展战略，组织制定人力资源整体战略规划和组织规划，为重大人事决策提供建议和信息支持;
3、组织公司的招聘工作并协调公司各岗位的人员安排，确保各重要岗位的人选;
4、制定和实施年度员工培训计划，并对培训效果进行评估;
5、组织制定公司的考核指标体系及相应的激励机制，了解行业薪酬福利水平及相关政策，制定符合公司实际情况的薪酬分配体系并组织实施;
6、协调员工与企业的关系，组织和推动企业文化建设。
7、进行人力结构分析，提出人力结构优化方案，协助各部门进行岗位调整，提高组织管理和运作效率。
任职要求:
1、本科及以上学历，人力资源管理，劳动经济、企业管理等相关专业优先。
2、工作经验要求:5年以上中型企业人力资源工作经验，3年以上人力资源经理岗位管理工作经验，有制造业从业经验优先;
3、对现代企业人力资源管理模式有系统的了解和丰富的实践经验;
4、对人力资源管理各个职能模块均有深入的认识，能够指导各个职能模块的工作;
5、 有半导体行业的人力资源，熟悉国家相关的政策、法律法规。
7、具有战略、策略化思维，有能力建立、整合不同的工作团队

MAIN OBJECTIVE OF THIS POSITION
This role will closely partner with retail management team to significantly increase the level of HR supports in recruitment, talent development, talent engagement in field, to continuously build retail capability and support the business development in region.

MAIN RESPONSIBILITIES OF THIS POSITION
Talent acquisition:
?	Explore retail recruitment channels and tracking effectiveness;
?	Explore qualified profession school for ECP program in key cities to build up young talent pipeline for field;
?	Set up monthly recruitment plan according to field priority needs to achieve monthly recruitment related KPI;
?	Train and coach integrated recruitment skills to retail management team to improve hiring efficiency and quality;

Talent development:
?	Be responsible to facilitate retail management team to implement well retail talent programs, include standard talent review process, individual develop plan tracking, succession plan, to build up internal talent pipeline for retail management positions;
?	Work with retail management team, promote and maintain company internal mobility system;
?	Conduct regular talent talk to digest &amp; refresh core talent training needs and feedback to Retail Academy;

Talent engagement:
?	Represent LVMH beauty group to promote corporate culture and conduct communication of all related employer branding information to retail team in region;
?	Implement talent engagement activities in region to enhance employee belonging to LVMH beauty group;
?	Recruitment related KPI
?	Internal promotion &amp; Mobility Successful Cases
?	Field staff turnover

PRINCIPAL COMPETENCIES, SKILLS AND BACKGROUND
Key competencies:
?	Performed effectively in a matrix, cross-functional and team environment;
?	Demonstrated customer/client focus;
?	Strong ability in project implementation and communication skills;
?	Focused on delivering excellence;
?	Creative and innovative;
?	Excellent entrepreneurial and teamwork spirit.

Technical skills:
?	Bachelor Degree or above
?	At least 8 years as a solid HR management role in large multi-national companies;
?	Experience in supporting clients in a variety of divisions, brands, of functions.
?	Expertise HR experience on talent acquisition or talent development;
?	Retail industry experience will be a plus
